reviews.text: Classic touristy place when in Davao. You can get crocodile and ostrich ice cream, crocodile lechon, civet coffee and other exotic delicacies. The fire show is entertaining but personally not one for zoos especially seeing the animals in small cages.

The Davao Crocodile park is large zoo located in Davao City. Aside from Crocodiles, they have a wide array of animals from Asia such as turtles, snakes, orangutans, birds, and more. They also have an Emu, a large Australian bird like the Ostrich. They have one of the largest crocodiles in captivity here. Check out the video of the large crocodile
Super cool to visit the area. Lots of fun to do. Great experienced to witnessed the fire dance.

Always a hit with the family, especially the kids! Aside from the main attraction Crocodiles, they have a ragtag collection of animals like birds of prey, colorful peafowls, lions and tigers, snakes(!!) And farm animals! The educational show was a lot of fun and the dancing crocodile show was unique. The kids love the feeding and petting of animals. We fed the crocs, the tiger, the koi fish, the ostrich and the rabbits! They're not for free but not expensive either, at 20-50pesos per "food". Definitely a great way to spend the day with the kids whether you local or a tourist :)
Nice. Could be feeding of the big one every day. Its hiding. But worth a visit.
The food was great. Good place for relaxing. You could also get a good view of the city. It is best to visit this place at night.
Nice and well maintained. Outstanding view at observation area.  Resto with view too.  Guard can call taxi when you are ready to leave. Good spot for photos.
Jack's Ridge doesn't disappoint. It's a great view and great food. The only negative was a tied up monkey without sufficient space to live a happy life.

A place worth remembering. 

The view is amazing at night!it's a fusion of Antipolo and Tagaytay minus the polluted air! When it comes to food and services, they were served fresh but we didn't have to wait that long!

Excellent service.

Good food at a very reasonable price!

Plus the group of singer's were so amazing that made us enjoyed the night while dining.. the waiter's & waitresses were approachable and can easily served our orders that fast! Last but not the least is your location that made it so interesting to view the place down there!

The place is awesome love it to be back good food nice ambiance no matter what the waiter acted for they are corrected for now after so many comments posted.

The experience here was so disappointing. We were served with PLASTIC PLATES and literally stacked PLASTIC GLASS. It’s a pricey restaurant but plastic wares? The place is crowded and noisy. The floor and comfort room is dirty.  The Karekare was another disappointment it looks good but doesn’t taste good at all.  The view is great but the location is far  with not much parking area.

If you are looking for somewhere inexpensive to have some lunch then come here as you have plenty to choose from. At this centre you cam buy almost anything from pork to chicken and everything in between and it will just cost under S$10 For a nice meal.
We have pork and duck meat with a pork soup and it was delicious. If you want to try something different then go for the black skin chicken. For drinks you can get anything from water to tea or coffee.
I had so much fun that hippies are so cool I smoke some of the best weed for the best price

A great space and part of Berkeley's story, student accommodation not sure? A refuge and a place of reflection for Berkeley siders, keep People's Park as it is, a moving story and inportant history that should be preserved and improved.

Peoples Park is a precious green space. I play live acoustic music at Peoples Park whenever I get a chance, guitar songs, jazz, funk, folk, rock, samba, bossa nova, percussion... I have old friends there and did community gardening there for five years, growing 13 foot tall corn and green beans, and all kinds of stuff. The trees and plants there are good old friends too. I've heard lots of great bands on the Free Speech Stage, summer concerts, the Berkeley World Music series, drum jams, dancing. Its very interesting, I've learned a lot there, talking to people, about history, people, culture, plants, gardening.

I have always loved this old park.
Sad it is always under attack and it is purposely kept decrepit by the University to justify building on it.
Guess everyone will use Williard Park should the unelected have their way.
It's a nice place to hang out. But the place gets very warm sometimes.

Shrine of the Holy Infant Jesus is one the places I have always loved to visit since I was a kid. It's one of the place I recommend you should visit,  there's this peace in the ambiance that I find comfort and solitude. Nowadays I find it hard to attend masses but I always see to it I light a candle here and say my thank you's, sorry's, and what I hope to have. You should try it too you'd feel great after.😊
The place is good, my family has been visiting here since 80s.
Shrine is one of a relaxing place I have been recognized while I was in Davao City.
Nice place to pray, meditate, or just sit and immerse yourself in nature.

Love the place so much, its really quite. And very rich with its history fro the old. I went here last year with friend we just drop by cause we have to leave right away going home. Yes its seems like a small but yes also you will feel the homey feeling when your inside the place specially if you're some who loves  history and arts being inside it was really cool..

It was fantastic to view the local history of Davao and it's inhabitants. The tour guide provided information and gave a good explanation in each gallery. The human sized figures gave a sense of realism and gave us the feeling of being in the moment. Such a great place to visit, with a local artist selling his works based on Filipino Culture. Anyone staying in Davao needs to see this, to fully understand how the people are what they are today.
Better be with tour guides who are not student OJT so that they can answer your questions very well.

This museum will show you the history of the province. It will introduce you of how it started as a small town up until how the livelihood progressed to a successful province we called now as Davao. 

You'll be accompanied by a guide all throughout the tour. Lot of tribes happened to live there back in the old days. The displays inside the museum, from vintage photos up to the real costumes worn by those tribes gave me chill. 

I liked the simplicity of this museum. There's no need for modern technoz to emphasize it's worth. The displays are enough to amaze me.. it feeds me the message naturally. The staffs were all approachable and accommodating too! 

*Taking picture is not really allowed in there; but there's few areas on which they let you take photos with.

A great place to visit in Davao, very educational. The Tour Guide we got was excellent, she really helped us learn a lot about the history of Davao. The tour itself took around half an hour, starting from the first floor to the second floor. 

And they have some nice, small paintings available at their souvenir shop from known artists which are very affordable. I must see not only for local tourists, but Davaoenos also.

Entrance is free, but I recommend giving a good tip to the guides especially if they have done a great job.

I feel like the pools should have its water replaced more often. The water smells like a large portion of it is urine. People dont shower before they enter the pool. If use your goggles underwater, you'd be able to see the dirt thats floating all around.
This place is average. Slightly common. Good for family bonding specially kids.
Expensive entrance rate. Didn't offer for overnight stay, small space, some were not-so-kind staff

This resort is a good place for family bonding and get together. They have pools for both kids and adults. Adults' pool is 4 feet in depth. I think they have 3 kiddie pools available wherein one of it do have slide. Kids and adult will difinitely have fun.

If you are looking for an escape but not far of the city this is the perfect place to visit. Exciting way to treat your children and celebrate your 🎂 birthday cause you'll be getting a free admission. 120 is the entrance fee for both adult and kids. Choose your cottage or make a reservation.

They serve frozen foods not "fresh" for the selection of their sashimi. If you priced them at 600++ for a platter at least give the courtesy to serve them fresh. Overpriced for a small portion of foods. Just overrated. Food also is not appetizing. Just utterly disappointed.
one of my fave place to eat. good food. nice people
Great food and quality service
Good food! Authentic Japanese cuisine...excellent customer service! Highly recommended.
Food is good and the weekday BOGO promo is awesome but if you dont finish your meal, you cant take it home. I sure hope they dont just throw away the left-overs.

Delicious food and reasonably priced! The service was very friendly and even helped finding fun locations to visit. Food was served with great portions quickly with a smile. Highly recommended for all type of consumers including vegan, vegetarian and meat eaters alike. Healthy options available.

I thought the food was very fresh and the fried rice was very refreshing it was a cute little treasure over the bridge. what is it the chicken puffs we're a little greasy but they were delicious. Very clean clean place to eat.

Decided to order some Thai food today for my birthday, I’ve heard nothing but good things about TukTuk so far.I ordered the crab Rangoon‘s and a chicken stirfry. I also decided to get a Thai iced tea as well. Everything from top to bottom was absolutely amazing the tea was perfectly sweet and delicious, and my favorite crab Rangoon‘s today. The chicken stirfry was cooked perfectly  with a beautiful blend of flavors. I would highly recommend 5out of 5 stars.
WOW!!!! Extremely flavorful- seriously the best Thai that I’ve ever EVER had! Also the delivery guy was super nice 😊

The food was pretty average and definitely not the best I've had. I thought it was overpriced, too. Especially for the amount of food. Maybe I'll try it again some time in the distant future to see if they improve but at the moment I don't really recommend trying.

Nice place to have a coffee, or food, and to do some work or a relaxed business meeting. They have decent Wi-Fi internet and there are many plugs for your chargers. (Note that as it is in a mall, it is a bit noisy) 
They have a bakery with tasty breads and cakes, and a kitchen that serves nice food, I ate there many times.
The waitresses are cute and polite, I just hope that the service will be faster.

Their Irish Cappuccino is superb! HOWEVER, their Fresh Fruit Salad is the worst salad that I ever ate so far! I suggest that they make sure their FRESH Fruit Salad is indeed FRESH! I hope their other customers will not be able to eat spoiled watermelon just like what we had. It's horrible! 
And one more thing, I suggest that they improve their service. I strongly recommend for their staffs to---as much as possible--attend to the needs of their customers immediately.
Very affordable with very accommodating staff.
If you love Taco then Taco Boy is your go to for a affordable and Yummy Taco!
Alberto's serves okay-tasting pizzas at very affordable prices.
The food is good but not the crew most specifically the frontdesk (person where you take your order) and place itself is quite stink and disorganised.
Fast delivery, fast service, taste good but the store and the screw i dont think so they follow food safety. Tables are dirty.
Their food is delicious given that they are also cheap.. best for budget delicious pizzas I recomend this branch for albertos pizza.!!!
Pizza is good but the service, it took us almost an hour before pizza was served.

The place is nice. The food is OK. The crew are friendly but the serving of food took too much time. Overall it is still a very nice place to eat specially when you are looking for grilled dishes and other pinoy cuisine.
loved it... ambience was great... food was wonderful and dwlicious...

It's a very spacious, open place. Wait staff are very courteous. Conveniently located along a major, busy road and a short walking distance to a major hospital. There are two sections: long tables for big group, and small tables for a more al fresco ambience. There's a good menu selection and the price is decent. However, I would not recommend this place on a hot day and during rain. Suggesting not to sit close to the windows or right next to the road. It can get noisy and dusty. Beggars would be asking for alm on the grills, and rain could come in if it's windy.
Food is great. Just don't like eating here at noon time because it's hot and you will literally sweat. Great place at night for barbeque and beer.
Good for hanging out with friends. They serve very cold beers.
A nice place with affordable price
authentic filipino food,swak s budget w/free bottomless ICE TEA
Nice food Busog much..
Nice
I like the foods but sometimes they need to upgrade the place and add some new foods to let the costumers be attract...

Very good Filpino and mixed cuisine.  Family.style Restaurant.  Very Restaurant was clean and staff very friendly and accommodating.  This was our trip to Twins and the have some best fried Hito (Catfish) and Curry Hi to around.  They serve Adobo Hito which I'll try on.our trip.  My Asawa loves their Fried Chicken and Special F-ried Rice-.  Good food prices and pleasurable dinning.  A good choice for dinning experience!,
Just ordinary an restaurant.
